Journeys end in lovers meeting.
—William Shakespeare, Twelfth Night
“漂泊止于爱人的相遇。”

The course of true love never did run smooth. 真爱无坦途。
——莎士比亚《仲夏夜之梦》


Lovers never meet. They're in each other all along. —— Rūmī，13世纪苏菲派穆斯林诗人
爱者不见，见诸于心

I love three things in the world / The sun,The moon and You / Sun for morning,Moon for night,and you forever —— 《暮光之城》
浮世三千，吾爱有三，日，月与卿。
日为朝，月为暮，卿为朝朝暮暮。
这句的翻译很美。

My apologies to an old lover for treating the new one as first.
—Wisawa Szymborska, Pod jedną gwiazdką
“我要向旧日的恋人道歉，因为我对新人如同初恋。”

You are my best hello and worst goodbye.


Yesterday is history
tomorrow is mystery
today is a gift
that's why it is called present
